HEADWORD: Pyralid
<hw>Pyr"a*lid</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>pyralis</ets>, <ets>-idis</ets>, a kind of winged insect.]</ety>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Any moth of the family <fam>Pyralid⟦ae⟧</fam>.
The species are numerous and mostly small, but some of them are very
injurious, as the bee moth, meal moth, hop moth, and clover
moth.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

